<p>div.code-sample code {
    overflow: auto;
    display: block;
    white-space:pre;
}</p>

<p>Also you may want to add the note from the Zend_Db Program Reference and a link to that section - <a href="http://framework.zend.com/manual/en/zend.db.html#zend.db.adapter">http://framework.zend.com/manual/en/…</a>:
"Each Zend_Db Adapter uses a PHP extension. You must have the respective PHP extension enabled in your PHP environment to use a Zend_Db Adapter. For example, if you use any of the PDO Zend_Db Adapters, you need to enable both the PDO extension and the PDO driver for the brand of RDBMS you use. "</p>

